    "description": "WITZ Corporation engages in the provision of control software engineering services in Japan. It operates in two segments, Software Business and Sensing Business. The company offers a range of embedded software for the automotive field; WiZNAR, a cybersecurity video seminar product; automotive cybersecurity education seminar products; functional safety support and cybersecurity response support solutions; and SF Twin Cobot, a simulation software for collaborative robots. It also provides WARXSS, a safety verification service for mobility; model-based development, 3D virtualization development, and plant simulation solutions; and SEAMS Guidelines, an AI quality and safety assurance product and solutions. The company was incorporated in 1997 and is headquartered in Nagoya, Japan."
